RO:0002310.definition: A process occurring within or in the vicinity of an organism that exerts some causal influence on the organism via the interaction between an exposure stimulus and an exposure receptor. The exposure stimulus may be a process, material entity or condition (for example, lack of nutrients). The exposure receptor can be an organism, organism population or a part of an organism.
RO:0002310.label: exposure event or process

GO:0007610.definition: The internally coordinated responses (actions or inactions) of animals (individuals or groups) to internal or external stimuli, via a mechanism that involves nervous system activity.
GO:0007610.label: behavior
GO:0007610.synonyms: behavioral response to stimulus;behaviour;behavioural response to stimulus

PCO:0000003.definition: A quality that inheres in a biological population.
PCO:0000003.label: quality of a population

PCO:0000018.synonyms: collection of organisms of the same species
PCO:0000018.definition: A material entity that has as parts two or more organisms, viruses, or viroids of the same species and no members of any other species.
PCO:0000018.label: single-species collection of organisms

PCO:0000001.definition: A collection of organisms, all of the same species, that live in the same place.
PCO:0000001.label: population of organisms

PCO:0000000.definition: A material entity that consists of two or more organisms, viruses, or viroids.
PCO:0000000.label: collection of organisms

PCO:0000005.definition: A process that has as primary participant a population.
PCO:0000005.label: population process

PCO:0000004.definition: A quality that inheres in a community.
PCO:0000004.label: quality of an ecological community

PCO:0000009.definition: The maximum number of individuals that can be supported in  a population that is growing according to logistic growth.
PCO:0000009.label: obsolete carrying capacity

PATO:0001241.synonyms: quality of a continuant;multiply inhering quality of a physical entity;monadic quality of a continuant;quality of continuant;quality of an object;quality of a single physical entity;monadic quality of an object;monadic quality of continuant
PATO:0001241.definition: A quality which inheres in a continuant.
PATO:0001241.label: physical object quality

ENVO:01001000.definition: An environmental system which is determined by a living organism.
ENVO:01001000.label: environmental system determined by an organism

BFO:0000020.definition: b is a specifically dependent continuant = Def. b is a continuant & there is some independent continuant c which is not a spatial region and which is such that b s-depends_on c at every time t during the course of b’s existence. (axiom label in BFO2 Reference: [050-003])
BFO:0000020.label: specifically dependent continuant

PATO:0001236.synonyms: relational quality of occurrent;quality of a process;quality of occurrent;quality of process
PATO:0001236.definition: A quality which inheres in an process.
PATO:0001236.label: process quality

BFO:0000023.definition: A realizable entity  the manifestation of which brings about some result or end that is not essential to a continuant  in virtue of the kind of thing that it is but that can be served or participated in by that kind of continuant  in some kinds of natural, social or institutional contexts.
BFO:0000023.label: role

GO:0044419.synonyms: interspecies interaction;interspecies interaction with other organisms;interaction with another species
GO:0044419.definition: Any process in which an organism has an effect on an organism of a different species.
GO:0044419.label: interspecies interaction between organisms

GO:0051816.label: acquisition of nutrients from other organism during symbiotic interaction

CARO:0001010.definition: Material anatomical entity that is a member of an individual species or is a viral or viroid particle.
CARO:0001010.label: organism or virus or viroid

PATO:0000322.definition: A color hue with high wavelength of the long-wave end of the visible spectrum, evoked in the human observer by radiant energy with wavelengths of approximately 630 to 750 nanometers.
PATO:0000322.label: red

IAO:0000409.definition: A denotator type indicates how a term should be interpreted from an ontological perspective.
IAO:0000409.label: denotator type

GO:0035176.definition: Behavior directed towards society, or taking place between members of the same species. Occurs predominantly, or only, in individuals that are part of a group.
GO:0035176.label: social behavior

ENVO:00003074.definition: A material entity that has been processed by humans or their technology in any way, including intermediate products as well as final products.
ENVO:00003074.label: manufactured product

PCO:0000010.definition: The number of different species represented in an ecological community.
PCO:0000010.label: community species richness

PATO:0001338.definition: A biological sex quality inhering in a population of multiple sexes.
PATO:0001338.label: mixed sex

PCO:0000012.definition: A population process that leads to an increase in the numbers of individuals in a population following a logistic (S-shaped) curve. Generally occurs when the population has a carrying capacity in a particular habitat.
PCO:0000012.label: logistic population growth

PCO:0000013.definition: A population growth process that leads to an exponential increase in the number of individuals in a population.
PCO:0000013.label: exponential population growth

RO:0002577.definition: A material entity consisting of multiple components that are causally integrated.
RO:0002577.label: system

GO:0051703.definition: Any process in which an organism has an effect on an organism of the same species.
GO:0051703.label: intraspecies interaction between organisms

GO:0051705.definition: Any process in which an organism has a behavioral effect on another organism of the same or different species.
GO:0051705.label: multi-organism behavior
GO:0051705.synonyms: behavioral interaction with other organism;behavioral interaction between organisms;behavioural interaction between organisms;behavioural interaction with other organism;behavioral signaling;behavioral signalling

GO:0051704.synonyms: physiological interaction between organisms;physiological interaction with other organism;interaction between organisms
GO:0051704.definition: A biological process which involves another organism of the same or different species.
GO:0051704.label: multi-organism process

BFO:0000015.definition: An occurrent that has temporal proper parts and for some time t, p s-depends_on some material entity at t.
BFO:0000015.label: process

BFO:0000017.definition: A specifically dependent continuant  that inheres in continuant  entities and are not exhibited in full at every time in which it inheres in an entity or group of entities. The exhibition or actualization of a realizable entity is a particular manifestation, functioning or process that occurs under certain circumstances.
BFO:0000017.label: realizable entity

ENVO:01000637.definition: Outer space is a hard vacuum containing a low density of particles, predominantly a plasma of hydrogen and helium as well as electromagnetic radiation, magnetic fields, neutrinos, dust and cosmic rays that exists between celestial bodies.
ENVO:01000637.label: outer space

PO:0000003.definition: A plant structure (PO:0005679) which is a whole organism.
PO:0000003.label: whole plant

ENVO:01000951.definition: An environmental system in which minimal to no anthropisation has occurred and non-human agents are the primary determinants of the system's dynamics and composition.
ENVO:01000951.label: natural environment

ENVO:01000952.definition: A process during which a natural environmental system is altered by human action.
ENVO:01000952.label: anthropisation

PCO:0000038.definition: A human social gathering at which two people are married. May include a legal or social ceremony.
PCO:0000038.label: wedding

PCO:0000039.definition: A human social gathering at which the key participant is an expectant parent and other guests bring presents for the soon to be born baby.
PCO:0000039.label: baby shower

PCO:0000020.definition: A domestic group, or a number of domestic groups linked through descent (demonstrated or stipulated) from a common ancestor, marriage, or adoption.
PCO:0000020.label: family

PCO:0000023.definition: A quality of a community that reflects how close in abundance all species in a community are.
PCO:0000023.label: community species evenness

PCO:0000022.definition: A process that ultimately leads to the death of all individuals in a population.
PCO:0000022.label: species extinction

PATO:0000117.definition: A morphology quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's physical magnitude.
PATO:0000117.label: size

PCO:0000029.definition: A collection of organisms that consists of two or more organisms from at least two species.
PCO:0000029.label: multi-species collection of organisms

PCO:0000028.definition: A collection of organisms of the same species whose members are all either genealogically related to each other or have mated with each other.
PCO:0000028.label: community

BFO:0000004.definition: A continuant that is a bearer of quality and realizable entity entities, in which other entities inhere and which itself cannot inhere in anything.
BFO:0000004.label: independent continuant

BFO:0000005.definition: A continuant  that is either dependent on one or other independent continuant  bearers or inheres in or is borne by other entities.
BFO:0000005.label: obsolete dependent continuant

BFO:0000002.definition: An entity that exists in full at any time in which it exists at all, persists through time while maintaining its identity and has no temporal parts.
BFO:0000002.label: continuant

BFO:0000003.definition: An entity that has temporal parts and that happens, unfolds or develops through time.
BFO:0000003.label: occurrent

ENVO:01000744.definition: A self-contained constructed feature used by one or more households as a home, such as a house, apartment, mobile home, houseboat or other 'substantial' structure. A dwelling typically includes nearby outbuildings, sheds etc. within the curtilage of the property, excluding any 'open fields beyond'. It has significance in relation to search and seizure, conveyancing of real property, burglary, trespass, and land use planning.
ENVO:01000744.label: human dwelling

PATO:0000051.definition: A quality of a single physical entity inhering in the bearer by virtue of the bearer's size or shape or structure.
PATO:0000051.label: morphology

PCO:0000032.definition: A collection of organisms of the same species whose members are all either genealogically related to each other or have mated with each other.
PCO:0000032.label: biological family

ENVO:02500000.definition: A process in which includes the components of an environmental system as participants.
ENVO:02500000.label: environmental system process

PCO:0000021.definition: A population process that ultimately leads to the death of all individuals in a population.
PCO:0000021.label: population extinction

PATO:0001291.definition: A physical quality that inheres in an bearer by virtue of how that bearer interacts with electromagnetic radiation.
PATO:0001291.label: electromagnetic (EM) radiation quality

PCO:0000033.definition: A type of social behavior in which a collection of humans intentionally gathers together on a temporary basis to engage socially.
PCO:0000033.label: human social gathering activity

PCO:0000030.definition: A household in which the majority of the income of its members is derived from agricultural activities.
PCO:0000030.label: agricultural household

PCO:0000031.definition: A material entity that is one or more organisms, viruses or viroids.
PCO:0000031.label: organismal entity

PCO:0000034.definition: A human social event in which humans living in the same area or neighborhood gather to carry out activiites relevent to the people living in the area.
PCO:0000034.label: human community event

PO:0025131.definition: An anatomical entity that is or was part of a plant.
PO:0025131.label: plant anatomical entity

GO:0008150.definition: Any process specifically pertinent to the functioning of integrated living units: cells, tissues, organs, and organisms. A process is a collection of molecular events with a defined beginning and end.
GO:0008150.label: biological_process

PCO:0000011.definition: A process that leads to a change in the number of individuals (positive or negative) in a population.
PCO:0000011.label: population growth

ENVO:00000002.definition:
An anthropogenic geographic feature is a geographic feature
resulting from the influence of human beings on nature.
ENVO:00000002.label: anthropogenic geographic feature

PATO:0000069.definition: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the whether the bearer differs from normal or average.
PATO:0000069.label: deviation(from_normal)

ENVO:01001002.definition: An environmental system determined by an animal.
ENVO:01001002.label: animal-associated environment

PATO:0002003.definition: A quality that inheres in an entire population or part of a population.
PATO:0002003.label: population quality

ENVO:01000817.definition: A biosphere is an environmental system which includes, as parts, all the living entities within the gravitational sphere of influence of an astronomical body, and the non-living and dead entities which they interact with.
ENVO:01000817.label: biosphere

PO:0009011.definition: An anatomical structure that is or was part of a plant, or was derived from a part of a plant.
PO:0009011.label: plant structure

ENVO:01000813.definition: A material part of an astronomical body.
ENVO:01000813.label: astronomical body part

ENVO:00002004.definition: An environmental feature that is, or can be, contained and is predominantly composed of one or a few types of stuff.
ENVO:00002004.label: mesoscopic physical object

PATO:0001739.definition: A quality that inheres in an bearer by virtue of how that bearer interacts with radiation.
PATO:0001739.label: radiation quality

ENVO:01000804.definition: An object which is composed of one or more gravitationally bound structures that are associated with a position in space.
ENVO:01000804.label: astronomical object

ENVO:02500027.definition: An environmental process which is driven by the action of humans.
ENVO:02500027.label: anthropogenic environmental process

PCO:0000002.definition: A community of at least two different species, living in a particular area. Must have at least two populations of different species as members.
PCO:0000002.label: ecological community

ENVO:01000254.definition: A system which has the disposition to environ one or more material entities.
ENVO:01000254.label: environmental system

RO:0002534.definition: Any entity that can be divided into parts such that each part is an atomical unit of a sequence
RO:0002534.label: sequence bearer

RO:0002533.definition: Any individual unit of a collection of like units arranged in a linear order
RO:0002533.label: sequence atomic unit

RO:0002532.definition: Any entity that is ordered in discrete units along a linear axis.
RO:0002532.label: sequentially ordered entity

PCO:1000002.definition: A population migration during which a population of humans moves from one area to another with the intention of settling permanently in the new location.
PCO:1000002.label: human population migration

PCO:1000003.definition: A migratory population of humans, travelling with the intention of settling in a new area.
PCO:1000003.label: human migratory population

PCO:1000000.definition: A population which is participating in a migration process.
PCO:1000000.label: migratory population

PCO:1000001.definition: A population process during which a population moves from one area to another.
PCO:1000001.label: population migration

ENVO:01001057.definition: An environmental system determined by part of a living or dead plant, or a whole small plant.
ENVO:01001057.label: environment associated with a plant part or small plant

PCO:1000004.definition: An ecological community which is composed of co-existing populations of microbial organisms that interact, directly or indirectly, such that they impact one another's ecological fitness.
PCO:1000004.label: microbial community

ENVO:01001055.definition: An environmental system determined by part of a living or dead animal, or a whole small animal.
ENVO:01001055.label: environment associated with an animal part or small animal

PATO:0000001.definition: A dependent entity that inheres in a bearer by virtue of how the bearer is related to other entities
PATO:0000001.label: quality

ENVO:01001110.definition: An environmental system which includes both living and non-living components.
ENVO:01001110.label: ecosystem

UBERON:0001062.definition: Biological entity that is either an individual member of a biological species or constitutes the structural organization of an individual member of a biological species.
UBERON:0001062.label: anatomical entity

PATO:0000161.definition: A quality of a single process inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's occurrence per unit time.
PATO:0000161.label: rate

PATO:0002301.definition: A quality that has a value that is decreased compared to normal or average.
PATO:0002301.label: decreased quality

PATO:0002303.definition: A quality of an object that has a value that is decreased compared to normal or average.
PATO:0002303.label: decreased object quality

ENVO:00010483.definition: A portion of environmental material is a fiat object which forms the medium or part of the medium of an environmental system.
ENVO:00010483.label: environmental material

CARO:0010004.definition: An individual member of a clade.
CARO:0010004.label: organism

IAO:0000078.definition: The curation status of the term. The allowed values come from an enumerated list of predefined terms. See the specification of these instances for more detailed definitions of each enumerated value.
IAO:0000078.label: curation status specification

IAO:0000102.definition: data about an ontology part is a data item about a part of an ontology, for example a term
IAO:0000102.label: data about an ontology part

PCO:0001001.label: pair of interacting organisms of the same species

PCO:0000024.definition: A material entity that consists of one or more people who live in the same dwelling and also share at meals or living accommodation, and may consist of a single family or some other grouping of people.
PCO:0000024.label: household

PATO:0001300.definition: An EM radiation quality in which the EM radiation is within the fiat range of the spectrum visible deemed to be light.
PATO:0001300.label: optical quality

ENVO:01000983.definition: An environmental system which includes, as parts, all the entities which have been constructed or manufactured by humans or their technology within the gravitational sphere of influence of an astronomical body.
ENVO:01000983.label: technosphere

IAO:0000225.definition: The reason for which a term has been deprecated. The allowed values come from an enumerated list of predefined terms. See the specification of these instances for more detailed definitions of each enumerated value.
IAO:0000225.label: obsolescence reason specification

PATO:0000014.definition: A composite chromatic quality composed of hue, saturation and intensity parts.
PATO:0000014.label: color

BFO:0000040.definition: An independent continuant that is spatially extended whose identity is independent of that of other entities and can be maintained through time.
BFO:0000040.label: material entity

PATO:0000587.definition: A size quality which is relatively low.
PATO:0000587.label: decreased size

PCO:0000035.definition: A human social gathering in which the intention is to have a good time. Often the intention is to celebrate something like a birthday, anniversary, or holiday, but there is not always a purpose.
PCO:0000035.label: party

PATO:0001018.definition: A quality of a physical entity that exists through action of continuants at the physical level of organisation in relation to other entities.
PATO:0001018.label: physical quality

ENVO:01000799.definition: An object which is naturally occuring, bound together by gravitational or electromagnetic forces, and surrounded by space.
ENVO:01000799.label: astronomical body

ENVO:00000070.definition: A feature that has been constructed by deliberate human effort.
ENVO:00000070.label: construction

PCO:0000019.definition: The number of different species that are represented in a given community, weighted by their abundance. Community species diversity can be calculated in different ways, but consists of two components: species richness and species evenness.
PCO:0000019.label: community species diversity

PCO:0000017.definition: A collection of organisms that has as parts every organism of given species and no organisms of any other species.
PCO:0000017.label: species as a collection of organisms

ENVO:01000313.definition: An anthropogenic environment is an environmental system which is the product of human activity.
ENVO:01000313.label: anthropogenic environment

ENVO:01000993.definition: A planned process during which raw or recycled materials are transformed into products for use or sale using labour and machines, tools, chemical and biological processing, or formulation.
ENVO:01000993.label: manufacturing process

ENVO:01000996.definition: An process during which natural or manufactured materials and products are processed and arranged by humans or their technology into structures.
ENVO:01000996.label: construction process

ENVO:01000997.definition: An environmental system which is determined by materials bearing roughly homogeneous qualities.
ENVO:01000997.label: environmental system determined by a quality

ENVO:01000998.definition: An environmental system within which an environmental material strongly influences the system's composition and properties.
ENVO:01000998.label: environmental system determined by a material

PATO:0001415.definition: A quality inhering in a population by virtue of the proportion of its members that are ill at a given time.
PATO:0001415.label: morbidity

PCO:0000027.definition: A collection of organisms of the same species that has as members only humans.
PCO:0000027.label: collection of humans

ENVO:00002297.definition: A material entity which determines an environmental system.
ENVO:00002297.label: environmental feature

BFO:0000031.definition: A continuant that is dependent on one or other independent continuant bearers. For every instance of A requires some instance of (an independent continuant type) B but which instance of B serves can change from time to time.
BFO:0000031.label: generically dependent continuant
